SIMPLE: troublesome
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Troublesome
<hw>Trou"ble*some</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <def>Giving trouble
or anxiety; vexatious; burdensome; wearisome.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>This <qex>troublesome</qex> world.</q> <rj><qau>Book of Common
Prayer.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>These <qex>troublesome</qex> disguises that we wear.</q>
<rj><qau>Milton.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>My mother will never be <qex>troublesome</qex> to me.</q>
<rj><qau>Pope.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><syn><b>Syn.</b> -- Uneasy; vexatious; perplexing; harassing;
annoying; disgusting; irksome; afflictive; burdensome; tiresome;
wearisome; importunate.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p>-- <wordforms><wf>Trou"ble*some*ly</wf>, <pos>adv.</pos> --
<wf>Trou"ble*some*ness</wf>, <pos>n.</pos></wordforms>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Troublous</ent>⟦br⟧
